properties.name: Spark de Triomphe
properties.description:
Ideas for rides can come from just about anywhere -- from maps or from history, from jokes or generative systems. Or, sometimes, they're simply stolen from somebody else. Yay, creativity!

This week we take "inspiration" from a series of walks exploring city parks led by longtime Passage rider John. Some of the parks we'll visit are newly designated and some are old; some are relatively large and some mere slivers, hardly even noticeable if one isn't paying attention. We'll see the trees and ride (and/or walk) the trails. We'll climb the hills and sway on the rope swings. And though many parts of the route come secondhand, we're sure the ride will be first-rate!
